"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is trying to plot date values on the x-axis, but Matplotlib requires these values to be converted to a format it can understand. Matplotlib has its own date handling functionality, but it requires manual conversion of the date values to Matplotlib's date format using the `date2num` function from `matplotlib.dates`. The `text` function also needs the x-coordinate to be in the same format.\",\n  \"patch\": \"15c15\\n<ax.plot(df['C'], df['E'])\\n---\\n>import matplotlib.dates as mdates\\n>ax.plot(mdates.date2num(df['C']), df['E'])\\n>ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))\\n17c17\\n<plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n>plt.text(mdates.date2num(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\")), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\"\n}"